  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best External SSD for Backup 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 6+ models</div>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <p>An external SSD is the difference between a backup you actually run and a backup you skip because it takes too long. Spinning hard drives max out around 130 MB/s, which means a 500GB backup takes an hour. A modern NVMe-based portable SSD completes the same transfer in under ten minutes, and survives being dropped in a bag without destroying your data. We evaluated six portable SSDs based on their published specifications, feature sets, and pricing to find the fastest, most durable, and most secure option.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 6 external SSD models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For speed, we assessed manufacturer-published sustained read/write specifications and benchmark claims. For durability, we evaluated drop resistance specifications, build material (aluminum vs plastic), and thermal management design. For encryption, we assessed security features based on manufacturer documentation, including hardware encryption availability and cross-platform software support.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Sustained read/write speeds and thermal throttling resistance</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Drop survival, thermal management, and connector durability</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-per-GB compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Setup, encryption, cross-platform compatibility</li>
      </ul>

