      </table>

      <h2 id="best-overall">Best Overall: Samsung T7 Portable SSD</h2>
      <p>The Samsung T7 won because it was the only drive in our comparison that delivered consistent sustained speeds without thermal throttling, combined with hardware encryption that actually works across all three major operating systems. Samsung claims 1050 MB/s read and 1000 MB/s write, and according to published benchmark data the drive achieves 1042 MB/s read and 986 MB/s write — essentially matching the spec, which is rare. More importantly, sustained write performance holds steady without the speed drop-off that occurs with cheaper drives after their cache fills.</p>
      <p>The aluminum unibody construction is what separates the T7 from plastic-bodied competitors. It dissipates heat through the chassis, which is why it sustains speed — plastic drives trap heat and throttle within 30-60 seconds of sustained writes. The T7 is rated for drop survival from desk height onto carpet, and the USB-C port is rated for 200+ plug cycles without loosening. At 58 grams and roughly credit-card-sized, it disappears into a pocket or laptop sleeve.</p>
      <p>The fingerprint security is the feature that elevates the T7 over equally-fast competitors. The embedded fingerprint sensor unlocks the drive on touch, and according to Samsung's specifications it recognizes a registered finger on the first try roughly 90% of the time, with a PIN fallback for wet or cold fingers. The included software works on Windows, Mac, and Android, and the drive ships with both USB-C to USB-C and USB-C to USB-A cables, so it connects to any device without an adapter. If you carry sensitive client files or personal documents in a bag, the fingerprint lock is genuine protection, not theater.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
